Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Lay the @British Streaky Bacon{6} in a single layer onto a lined #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden brown and crispy, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Once cooked, remove from the oven.

Meanwhile, tear the @Ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks and pop onto another baking tray.

Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat well. Spread out in a single layer.

Bake the croutons on the top shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the oven and set aside.

While the bacon and croutons bake, drain the @Sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

Once charred, remove from the heat.

Chop the @Medium Tomato{2} into 1cm pieces. Cut the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%g} into 1cm cubes.

Halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a board, face-down. Slice into 1cm thick slices - you'll fan it out later.

In a large #salad bowl{}, combine the @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1.5%tbsp} for the dressing with the @Cider Vinegar{30%ml}. Season with salt and pepper, then mix together.

When everything is ready, chop the crispy bacon into bite-size pieces and add half to the dressing bowl, along with the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%g}, tomatoes, sweetcorn, Greek style salad cheese and croutons. Toss to coat.

Share the salad between your #bowls{}. Scatter over the remaining bacon and fan out the sliced avocado on top.

Drizzle over the @Mayonnaise{1}(loosened with a splash of water if needed) to finish. Enjoy!